first_step=wash chilli and cut into pieces
second=Heat the oil in a frying pan until hot. 
third=Add the chili peppers, tomato, salt, and water and cover with a lid. Cook for 8 minutes or until the peppers are tender
fourth=Add the cheese and stir until it’s melted into the sauce. If you want to make it even richer, you can mix in a pat of butter at the end.
fifth=Serve Ema Datshi with rice
